<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-06-13T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-06-13T14:00:00-05:00" n="175" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d175">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/1887</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Francis</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-06-13T15:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">June 13,
                                            1918, 3 p.m.</hi></date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>179. Your 185, May 20, 5 p.m. You are authorized to draw on the
                                Department up to $5,000,000 additional to $1,000,000 already
                                allotted for the same purpose. You are to report progress at
                                frequent intervals. Funds are to be expended only for such supplies
                                as can be controlled to the point of moving them in safety towards
                                Archangel or Vladivostok. Department assumes that members of <pb facs="0177" n="127" xml:id="pg_127"/> purchasing commission will
                                enlist cooperation of consular service and of the British and French
                                to follow shipments and report at once if their safety is imperiled
                                or success of efforts liable to fail of realization.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_LR1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>